{
  "stem": "27351.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 14.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "However, my-- my parents did speak Yiddish occasionally among themselves.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my father was-- he was-- he was a real polyglot, and every language he spoke was absolutely beautiful.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He-- but he was called-- he was a [YIDDISH], and I don't know how to translate it into English, but it means that she really loved Jewish culture, the Yiddish language, and he wrote a lot in Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He also wrote in Polish, and-- and in his Polish writings, I remember the verses, the poems, that he would send us.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And some of them were sent-- he once had a long term in jail.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I was only 3 then.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we were receiving from jail these beautiful little poems in Polish for children, and I still remember them.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh yes, I could.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It will take maybe two minutes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was-- my mother sent him a picture of the two children just holding hands together, and he sent back this beautiful piece of paper with a drawing of this picture, only on this drawing, we wore masks.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the little poem was called [POLISH].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It means 'Who are you?' And it goes like that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[SPEAKING POLISH]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This is the verse, and basically what it means is he speculates who we could be, who we are.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Are we rich?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Or are we poor?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Are we, maybe, some terrible bandits, like Alibaba and others?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Or maybe we are little rebels who would like to build a new, good life all over the world.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he promises that he will never tell anybody, so please tell.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's-- my husband used a very sophisticated language in everyday language that he spoke.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't, obviously, understand the words, but anyone could hear the rhythm and the music and the rhyming--",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh yeah, there is a rhyming, yeah.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
